  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d85\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dda \u0d9c\u0db6\u0da9\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Paddy in Polonnaruwa is rotting in a warehouse in Ampara",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Mahaweli B Zone Farmers' Organization says that an excessive stock of 65,000 kilos of paddy bought in the 2015 yala season is rotting in an Aralagangwila warehouse.",
        "Mr. Sarath Rajapaksa, the former secretary of Mahaweli B Zone Business Committee, said that the stock of rice purchased from Aralagangwila, Vijayapura and Polonnaruwa in Mahaweli B Zone, which was opened in 2015, is currently being destroyed in the warehouse.",
        "Some of the paddy stocks are rotten and due to the broken roofs, the water has mixed with the rice stocks and the local residents have also alleged that the rice stocks have sprouted.",
        "Farmers allege that this paddy warehouse, which was opened in 2015, has bought paddy only once, and another newly built warehouse nearby has not yet been opened.",
        "Mr. Sarath Rajapaksa, the former secretary of Mahaweli B Group's business committee, said that these paddy stocks were bought from farmers in the 2015 yala season.",
        "Farmers also alleged that wild elephants are harmful to this paddy store and some people have tried to remove the plates of the store.",
        "Mr. Sarath Rajapaksa further said that he would also request the relevant authorities to prepare the warehouses to buy paddy from the farmers of Vijayabapura division in Mahaweli B zone this year.",
        "The representatives of the Mahaweli B region farmers' organizations requested that the President, the Prime Minister and the Minister of Agriculture should pay immediate attention to this and initiate a program to take advantage of it.",
        "In this regard, when we inquired from Mr. Nimal Ekanayake, the Polonnaru District Manager of the Marketing Board over the phone, he said that the warehouses are complex and are under the Ampara Manager of the Marketing Board.",
        "Accordingly, in a telephone inquiry with Mr. Shanta Kumara, Ampara District Manager of Aap Paddy Marketing Board, he stated as follows.",
        "A pile of rotten rice rots in the said shed. There are about 5000 kilos. Those removed from V bags are everywhere in the M store. The release of the Abili V has to be given through a committee.",
        "Due to lack of service in the Polonnaruwa district of the Marketing Board, during the yala season of 2015, Aralagangwila and Vijaya Pura Vi Togo Ampara employees were employed and purchases were made. Mr. Shanta Kumara also said that as soon as the money is received, the Polonnaruwa offices will pay the money and buy them."
      ],
